.TH GIT\-PICKDIR 1 "" "git-pickdir 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-pickdir \- extract subdirectories into a new repo with history flattened to root
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git-pickdir
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
\fIREPODIR\fR
\fISUBDIRS\fR...
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBgit-pickdir\fR extracts one or more subdirectories from the current Git
repository into a new repository. Selected paths are flattened to the
repository root and history is rewritten (using \fBgit-filter-repo\fR(1)) so
that only those paths remain.
.PP
Must be run inside a valid Git repository with at least one commit.
Repository root is detected with \fBgit rev-parse \-\-show-toplevel\fR.
.PP
\fIREPODIR\fR is the target directory for the new repository; it must not
already exist.
.PP
\fISUBDIRS\fR are repository-relative paths to directories to extract (e.g.
\fIsrc/lib\fR, \fIinclude/common\fR). Trailing slashes are normalized. No
subdirectory may be a prefix of another. If flattening would produce the same
filename from different subdirs, the command fails.
.SH COPY STRATEGY
If the current repository is "fresh" (no loose objects under
\fI.git/objects\fR and no remotes), \fBgit-pickdir\fR uses \fBcp \-a\fR for a
fast copy. Otherwise it uses \fBgit clone \-\-no-local\fR to avoid hardlinks.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Exits non-zero and prints to stderr if:
.IP \(bu 2
Not run inside a Git repository
.IP \(bu 2
Repository has no commits
.IP \(bu 2
\fIREPODIR\fR already exists
.IP \(bu 2
No \fISUBDIRS\fR provided
.IP \(bu 2
Any \fISUBDIR\fR does not exist at HEAD
.IP \(bu 2
\fISUBDIR\fR is absolute or contains \fI..\fR
.IP \(bu 2
One subdir is a prefix of another
.IP \(bu 2
Filename collision when flattening
.IP \(bu 2
\fBgit-filter-repo\fR is not installed or not in PATH
.IP \(bu 2
A Git or filter-repo command fails
.IP \(bu 2
No files remain after filtering
.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
git-pickdir ../newrepo src/lib include/common
.EE
Creates \fI../newrepo\fR with only the contents of \fIsrc/lib\fR and
\fIinclude/common\fR at the repository root and history preserved for those
paths.
.SH REQUIREMENTS
\fBgit\fR(1) \(>= 2.x and \fBgit-filter-repo\fR must be installed and on PATH.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgit\fR(1), \fBgit-filter-repo\fR(1), \fBgit-clone\fR(1)
